cs.CL, cs.IR, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.SI

This paper deals with topic modeling, which is a subfield of natural language processing (NLP) and information retrieval (IR). Therefore, cs.CL (Computation and Language) and cs.IR (Information Retrieval) are the most likely sub-categories. The paper also proposes a new measure for quantifying the stability of LDA models, which involves clustering techniques. This suggests that the paper may also be relevant to cs.LG (Machine Learning) and cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence), which are closely related to clustering. Finally, the paper discusses an application to real data consisting of newspaper articles, which suggests that it may also be relevant to cs.SI (Social and Information Networks).
